-- MOVES-Amundi Smith Breeden hires Kenneth Monaghan from Rogge Global Partners
-- 
-- Mon Sep 15, 2014 12:06PM EDT
-- None



Sept 15 (Reuters) - Amundi Smith Breeden, the U.S. fixed income management unit of asset management company Amundi, appointed Kenneth Monaghan as head of its international high yield bond management team.

Previously, Monaghan worked at Rogge Global Partners in the United States, where he was responsible for high yield fixed income activities.   (Bangalore newsroom: moves@thomsonreuters.com)  Keywords: AMUNDI MOVES/KENNETHMONAGHAN